OL,3,CSwindon South MP Heidi Alexander
OL,4,Cappointed Transport Secretary
OL,6,FShe had initially reported to police
OL,7,Fthat her work phone device had been
OL,8,Fstolen, but claims she discovered
OL,9,F"some time later" that the device had
OL,10,Fnot been taken and that she had made a
OL,11,F"genuine mistake", from which she "did
OL,12,Fnot make any gain".
OL,14,F"The original work device being
OL,15,Fswitched on triggered police attention
OL,16,Fand I was asked to come in for
OL,17,Fquestioning. My solicitor advised me
OL,18,Fnot to comment during that interview
OL,19,Fand I regret following that advice."
